Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the garlic, @Central American Style Spice Mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @tomato puree{30%g} to the mince. Stir-fry for ~{1%min}. IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @water for the sauce{75%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%mins}.

Once thickened, taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Meanwhile, preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Halve the @lime{1}.

== Tomato Salsa ==

Chop the @medium tomato{1} into small pieces and pop into a #medium bowl{}.

Drizzle over a little @olive oil{some}, squeeze in some lime juice, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together.

Cut any remaining lime into wedges.

== Assembly ==

Just before you're ready to serve, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%mins}.

When everything's ready, lay the tortillas onto your #serving plates{} (3 per person).

Make your tacos by starting with the baby gem, then add spoonfuls of the mince, cheese and tomato salsa - as much as you'd like.

Finish with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}.

Serve the lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.

> TIP: Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!